HEADWORD: joewood
<hw>joewood</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>A West Indian shrub or small tree
(<spn>Jacquinia keyensis</spn>) having leathery saponaceous leaves and
extremely hard wood.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> barbasco, <spn>Jacquinia keyensis</spn>.</syn>⟦br⟧
